Unix Timestamp conversion tools

Convert epoch to human-readable date and vice versa.

The Unix epoch (or Unix time or POSIX time or Unix timestamp) is the number of seconds that have elapsed since January 1, 1970 (midnight UTC/GMT)

https://www.epochconverter.com/

C data structure to represent time is -
	struct	timeval currenttime;

Call function, pass data structure as argument.
	gettimeofday(&currenttime, NULL);
returns time in seconds.

To convert it to milliseconds -

millisecs	=	currenttime.tv_sec * 1000 	+ 	currenttime.tv_usec / 1000;
	c						a									b

a) currenttime.tv_sec * 1000: 
	This part of the formula converts the time represented 
	in seconds (currenttime.tv_sec) to milliseconds. 
	1 second equals 1000 milliseconds
b) currenttime.tv_usec / 1000: 
	This part of the formula converts the microseconds component
	 (currenttime.tv_usec) to milliseconds. 
	To convert microseconds to milliseconds, you divide by 1000.
c) 	By adding these two components together, you obtain the total time 
	in milliseconds.
